    {
      "id": "16a9980c_8837ad89",
      "file_path": "vid-webpack-master/src/app/shared/utils/iframe.service.ts",
      "patchset_number": 9,
      "line": 47,
      "message": "this is not bullet-proof because of the following: \n\nhttps://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/frameElement\nif the document into which it's embedded has a different origin, the value is null\n\nso if there is a parent, on same origin -- there is a value which is not null, even if not VID\n\n\nour cases are: \n\n1) self is inside vid's angular iframe -> return true\n2) self is only inside portal's iframe -> return false\n3) self is on top -> return false\n\n\nI suggest adding an id to file app/vid/scripts/view-models/iframe.htm , e.g.:\n<iframe ng-src=\"{{url}}\" id=\"vidAngularEmbed\"></iframe>\n\nand then doing here:\n\nreturn window.frameElement && window.frameElement.id === \"vidAngularEmbed\"",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4379,
        "name": "Ittay Stern",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ittay.stern@att.com",
        "username": "ittays"
